subject: Track and Field
lead_paragraph: The pole-vaulter Yelena Isinbayeva of Russia and the 400-meter runner Sanya Richards of the United States shared the $1 million jackpot when they won their events yesterday in Berlin at the season’s final Golden League meet. Isinbayeva cleared 15 feet 9 ¾ inches. Richards won in 49.27 seconds, the fastest time this year.
